3-for-3 and Al Martin drove in two runs as the San Diego Padres beat the
slumping Colorado Rockies 5-1 Friday night. Eaton (2-1), who won on May 30
against Milwaukee and had seven no-decisions since, fanned three, walked four
and gave up a run and seven hits in 7 1-3 innings, his longest stint of the
year. The 22-year-old right hander also walked and became the first Padres
pitcher in over five years to steal a base. Martin had a two-run single. Ryan
Klesko, Damian Jackson and Ruben Rivera added RBI hits.
