Mexico, U.S. Make Transplant Pact
</SUBHEAD>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- The U.S. transplant network agreed Friday to share with
Mexico its experience in distributing organs, inaugurating an information
exchange that officials hope will boost Mexico's less-developed system and help
Americans increase Hispanic donations. The formal agreement, signed Friday in
Mexico City, was not necessary from the American point of view, given that the
U.S. network regularly shares information with other nations. But Mexican
authorities wanted to establish a formal relationship. The agreement is meant to
help Mexico's National Transplant Council develop a nationwide system for
distributing organs.
</P>
