four walks and an error in knocking out Matt Perisho (2-3) in the opening
inning. Paul Abbott (6-3) blanked the Rangers until Frank Catalonotto led off
the sixth with a home run. Texas played without catcher Ivan Rodriguez. Manager
Johnny Oates decided his slumping All-Star a night off.
AP NewsBrief by PAULINE M. MILLARD 
