<HEADLINE> Former Nassau Democratic chair sentenced to 8 years in prison  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   HAUPPAUGE, N.Y. (AP) - Former Nassau Democratic County Chair
Stephen Sabbeth, who was convicted in March 1999 of bankruptcy
fraud, was sentenced to 97 months in prison Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Sabbeth is to remain free on bail until September 22, when he
must surrender at a facility to be named later. The eight-year,
one-month sentence is on a money laundering charge. He was also
given five 60-month sentences, to be served concurrently, on other
charges.
</P>
<P>
   In 1997, Sabbeth was charged in an 11-count indictment with
concealing more than $750,000 from creditors before declaring the
family's lumber business bankrupt in 1990.
</P>
<P>
   After his release, Sabbeth will have three years to repay
$125,000 to the banks he was convicted of defrauding.
</P>
<P>
   Sabbeth chaired the Nassau Democratic Party from 1993 until his
resignation last year, a few weeks after his conviction.
</P>
</TEXT>
