<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Elizabeth school board member charged with sex assault on teen  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ELIZABETH, N.J. (AP) - A member of the city's Board of Education
faces sexual assault charges for allegedly having intercourse with
a teen-age girl for four years, beginning when she was 10 years
old.
</P>
<P>
   David Lewis, 33, was arrested Thursday and charged with three
counts of aggravated sexual assault on a minor. He was being held
in the Union County Jail in lieu of $50,000 bail.
</P>
<P>
   Lt. Daniel Saulnier said the Lewis did not know the girl through
his position on the school board, or his position as a youth
minister at the Shiloh Baptist Church in Elizabeth.
</P>
<P>
   He was elected to a three-year term on the board in April.
</P>
<P>
   His lawyer, Robert Ungvary, said Lewis was falsely accused by
the girl, who is now 14 years old.
</P>
<P>
   ''I understand there is no physical evidence of any abuse,'' he
said. ''He vehemently denies any abuse, and there is no third party
who witnessed the abuse.''
</P>
<P>
   Ungvary said the girl told police the most recent assault took
place about two weeks ago. He also said Lewis has no plans to
resign from the board.
</P>
</TEXT>
