<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jersey City parking officer accused of bribery  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   JERSEY CITY, N.J. (AP) - A city parking violations officer is
accused of soliciting bribes from motorists in exchange for not
issuing summonses.
</P>
<P>
   Akema Campbell, 20, was arrested Friday and charged with bribery
and official misconduct.
</P>
<P>
   Police said she offered not to write tickets to violators if
they paid her the fines on the spot.
</P>
<P>
   She was suspended after her arrest and released on her own
recognizance.
</P>
<P>
   ''It's only allegations, but something like this could not be
expected,'' said Parking Authority Executive Director Carmine
Venezia. ''I'm extremely disappointed, and I feel bad for the
public because it's a public trust issue.''
</P>
<P>
   Police said Campbell patrols the city's downtown section,
looking for parking violations.
</P>
<P>
   Her arrest came about a year after another city parking officer
was charged with writing more than 400 phony tickets.
</P>
</TEXT>
