<HEADLINE> Lineup for the Sunday TV News Shows  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Lineup for the Sunday TV news shows:
</P>
<P>
   ABC's ''This Week With Sam Donaldson and Cokie Roberts'' --
Topics: Campaign 2000, Mideast summit, tax cuts and gays in the
military. Guests: White House chief of staff John Podesta; Karl
Rove, chief Bush campaign strategist; Mark Fabiani, Gore deputy
campaign manager for communications; military sociologist Charles
Moskos and Pat Kutteles, mother of slain Pfc. Barry Winchell.
(Note: Program may air at other than usual time because of British
Open coverage. Check local listings.)
</P>
<P>
   CBS' ''Face the Nation'' -- Topic: Campaign 2000. Guests: Karl
Rove, chief Bush campaign strategist; Jack Quinn, Gore adviser;
Scott Reed, former Elizabeth Dole campaign chairman; and William
Bennett, Republican activist.
</P>
<P>
   NBC's ''Meet the Press'' -- Topic: Campaign 2000. Karen Hughes,
Bush senior adviser; Bob Shrum, Gore adviser; and Sens. Chuck
Hagel, R-Neb., and Dick Durbin, D-Ill.
</P>
<P>
   CNN's ''Late Edition With Frank Sesno'' -- Topic: Campaign 2000,
congressional politics and the New York Senate race. Guests: Mark
Fabiani, deputy Gore campaign manager for communications; Karl
Rove, chief Bush campaign strategist; Sens. Don Nickles, R-Okla.,
and Dick Durbin, D-Ill; Mike Murphy, Lazio for Senate campaign
strategist; Mark Green, New York City's public advocate.
</P>
<P>
   ''Fox News Sunday'' -- Topic: Projected budget surplus, tax cuts,
Campaign 2000. Guests: House Majority Whip Tom DeLay, R-Texas;
White House budget chief Jack Lew; Karen Hughes, Bush campaign
communications director; and Ron Klain, senior Gore adviser.
</P>
</TEXT>
