<P>
   ''Everyone likes her very much,'' said temple treasurer Seymour
Siegel. ''They're just disturbed about her passion with the PLO and
her history with those causes.''
</P>
<P>
   He was apparently referring to the first lady's embrace of
Arafat's wife, Soha, after she had made a speech accusing Israeli
troops of using poison gas on Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
   Worshipper Amy Gross disagreed.
</P>
<P>
   ''I thought she was wonderful,'' Gross said. ''I thought she's
truly hoping for the same peace we all are.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
