<HEADLINE> Hedy Lamarr Adopted Son Fights Will  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SANFORD, Fla. (AP) -- The estranged adopted son of Hedy Lamarr
has challenged the actress' will, which left him nothing.
</P>
<P>
   James Lamarr Loder, 61, of Omaha, wants the screen siren's will
thrown out so he can be put in charge of her $3 million estate.
</P>
<P>
   Loder alleged that Lamarr was ''of unsound mind'' when she
signed her last will Nov. 3. He also claimed the will was the
result of ''fraud, duress, coercion or undue influence'' by those
named in the will.
</P>
<P>
   The attorney who drafted the will said Lamarr was alert and knew
exactly what she was doing when she signed the will three months
before her death at age 85 in January.
</P>
<P>
   The will leaves about $1.8 million to Lamarr's son, Anthony
Loder, and $1.2 million to her daughter, Denise Loder-DeLuca. Four
friends received about $83,000 each.
</P>
<P>
   How Lamarr and Loder became estranged is unclear and whether
they reconciled before her death is uncertain.
</P>
</TEXT>
