<HEADLINE> Postage Stamp To Honor Lucille Ball  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BURBANK, Calif. (AP) -- America's favorite redhead will be
showing up in mailboxes across the country.
</P>
<P>
   A stamp honoring Lucille Ball was unveiled Friday at the
''Loving Lucy 2000'' fan convention. The stamp is scheduled for
release in 2001.
</P>
<P>
   The stamp's color illustration shows the late ''I Love Lucy''
actress sporting masses of curly red hair and a bejeweled earring,
based on a 1955 photograph.
</P>
<P>
   With a Lucy impersonator standing by, actor Karl Malden, a
member of the Citizens' Stamp Advisory Committee, helped unveil the
stamp, the second to feature the actress.
</P>
<P>
   She appeared with her late husband, Desi Arnaz, on a stamp
commemorating ''I Love Lucy'' in the Postal Service's ''Celebrate
the Century'' series.
</P>
<P>
   The new stamp is the seventh in a ''Legends of Hollywood''
series. Marilyn Monroe, James Dean and Humphrey Bogart are among
other Hollywood icons who have been featured.
</P>
