<HEADLINE> Woman Who Entered Pitt's Home Sought  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- A $5,000 arrest warrant has been issued for a
woman convicted of trespassing at the Hollywood Hills home of actor
Brad Pitt.
</P>
<P>
   The warrant for Athena M. Rolando was activated after she twice
failed to appear for a court hearing on her progress in undergoing
counseling, the city attorney's office said Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Rolando climbed into Pitt's home through a rear window last year
while the actor was away. A caretaker found her wearing Pitt's
clothes and sleeping in an upstairs bedroom.
</P>
