<HEADLINE> Obituaries in the News  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated PressJonathan Kiser:
<TEXT>
<P>
   BALTIMORE (AP) -- Jonathan Kiser, the leading steeplechase rider
in the country with 16 victories in 55 mounts, died Friday from
severe head injuries after an accident at his sister's home. He was
22.
</P>
<P>
   Kiser won his first race in 1994 and won two riding
championships in the last three seasons. He had been expected to
ride several horses for prominent steeplechase trainer Tommy Voss
during the upcoming Saratoga meeting.
Roberto Suarez Gomez:
</P>
<P>
   LA PAZ, Bolivia (AP) -- Roberto Suarez Gomez, a drug trafficker
who called himself the ''King of Cocaine'' and claimed to be the
model for a character in the movie ''Scarface,'' died Thursday from
a heart attack, his family said. He was 68.
</P>
<P>
   Suarez Gomez played a major role in the expansion of cocaine
trafficking in Bolivia, and gained notoriety in 1983 when he
offered to pay the country's foreign debt of $3 billion with
proceeds from cocaine trafficking.
</P>
<P>
   He was also a main financial supporter of a military regime that
held power from 1980 to 1982.
</P>
<P>
   Suarez Gomez's downfall came in 1988 when he was sentenced to 15
years for drug crimes. He was released early, in 1996.
</P>
<P>
   By his death, most of his vast fortune had dissipated and the
one-time drug lord said he was repentant.
Virginia F. Saurwein:
</P>
<P>
   ERIE, Pa. (AP) -- Virginia F. ''Ginny'' Saurwein, a former United
Nations official who founded the Women's World Banking
organization, which provided loans to low income women in
developing countries, died July 9. She was 72.
</P>
<P>
   Saurwein joined the staff of the U.S. Committee for the U.N. as
program director and continued those duties with the merged U.N.
Association of the United States.
</P>
<P>
   In 1975, she became chief of the Non-Governmental Organization
Liaison Unit in the U.N. Department of Economic and Social Affairs,
the chief non-governmental post in the U.N. She retired in 1989.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-07-22-00 1843 </TRAILER>
