<HEADLINE> Blazing Sword Wins at Arlington  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ARLINGTON HEIGHTS, Ill. (AP) -- Blazing Sword beat Mula Gula by a
length Saturday in the Grade II Washington Park Handicap at
Arlington International Racecourse.
</P>
<P>
   Blazing Sword, ridden by Jose Rivera, ran 1 1-8 miles in
1:50.59, and paid $22.80, $7.00 and $4.40. Mula Gula returned $3.60
and $2.80, and Nite Dreamer paid $3.80 to show.
</P>
<P>
   The victory, worth $150,000 of the $250,000 purse, boosted the
career earnings of the 6-year-old gelding to $1.158 million. It was
the 11th victory in 42 starts for the son of Sword Dancer.
</P>
</TEXT>
