<HEADLINE> Gallo Blue Chip Wins 2nd Round  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   YONKERS, N.Y. (AP) -- Gallo Blue Chip, already the winner of the
Meadowlands Pace and North America Cup this year, went wire-to-wire
in 1:53 2-5 Saturday night to win the second elimination in the Art
Rooney Pace at Yonkers Raceway.
</P>
<P>
   Driven by Dan Dube, the three-year-old gelding by Musical Mike
qualified for next Saturday's $319,164 final.
</P>
<P>
   The elimination victory was worth $26,596 and boosted Gallo Blue
Chip's earnings for the year to $345,700 and lifetime to
$1,613,156. He has seven wins in 11 starts this year after going
undefeated in eight races in 1999.
</P>
<P>
   Profita was second, followed by Cinnamon Place and High On
Emotion to fill out half of the entry for the eight-horse final.
</P>
<P>
   Macart, with Dave Miller, won the opening elimination in a
slower 1:54 3-5. With Held, Mystical Mike and The Blue Pan Group
trailed Macart across the finish line to complete the field for the
title race.
</P>
<P>
   The Art Rooney Pace is named in memory of the former owner of
the Pittsburgh Steelers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
